-- 
BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Vale Reports Earnings, Copom Minutes

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-07-28T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/brazil-daybook-vale-reports-earnings-copom-minutes.html
Vale, the world’s largest iron-ore
producer, releases second-quarter earnings results after the  Sao
Paulo  market close. The mean estimate for net income by five
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was 10 billion reais as of
yesterday.  The central bank releases the minutes of last week’s
monetary policy meeting, which may signal the outlook for
 interest rates  or other measures.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff attends the inauguration ceremony of
Peruvian President Ollanta Humala in Lima at 10:30 a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega and central bank President
Alexandre Tombini attend a meeting of the monetary policy
council, Copom, at 3 p.m.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Petrobras CEO Jose Sergio Gabrielli and  Haroldo Lima , head of
Brazil’s national oil regulation agency, speak at an event in
Rio de Janeiro. Lima will speak at 9 a.m., Gabrielli at 10 a.m.  ECONOMY:
*FGV Inflation IGP-M (MoM) at 8 a.m.
*FGV Inflation IGP-M (YoY) at 8 a.m.
*Copom monetary policy meeting minutes at 8:30 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Embraer (EMBR3 BZ) before market.
*Vale (VALE5 BZ) after market.  EQUITIES:
*Braskem (BRK5M BZ) agreed to buy Dow Chemical’s polypropylene
assets for $323.
*Petrobras (PETR4 BZ) was granted a 1.1 billion-real loan from
the national  development bank  for the Refap refinery.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 1.8 percent to 58,288.46.
*The real fell 1.06 percent to 1.5556 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robin Stringer in Sao Paulo at 
 rstringer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
